cc:Work.dc:title: Fox Frame
cc:Work.dc:description: This frame of foxes, or dare I say Fabulously Foxy Fox Frame, was synthesized from an advertisement in a 1920s newspaper for fur coats. Actually, I combined it with elements from another coat ad, which I thought looked better, and ended up with a Celtic inspired fox frame with no bottom. Now this is so oddly specific, I would be fascinated if anyone actually can find a use for it. Enjoy!
